```{% for choice in hubdb_table_column(2664478, 4).options %}
&lt;div class="checkbox"&gt;
&lt;input type="checkbox" value=".{{ choice.name|replace(' ','-')|lower }}"&gt; &lt;label class="checkbox-label"&gt;{{ choice.name }}&lt;/label&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
{% endfor %}```
I'm using the code above to display the options within a multi-select hubdb table; if I only want to show the options for rows of a certain type, how would I do that? I tried wrapping the div in `{% if row.form_type__contains=Loss Prevention %}` and got a number of errors. Do you have any recommendations?
